	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99765813692714><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj>My AC Story</span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=75540><span id=Scholar>Darkfever</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>78 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Aug 12th 7:15 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, i guess when you see this you think&nbsp;&nbsp;(ahh geez  not another walked into zone saw the ac killed it bam  only 5 mins) type story...  I was actually at the camp around 6 hours before i got him..  I just got my ring last night... well this morning.. and i am glad to finally get that out of the way..  I chose So Ro cuz its an easier spawn to solo... Overall i have spent about 30 hours here... Not all together but i tried at 40 and 42 a couple times  but last night i figured i had nothing better to do  so what the hell...<br><br>If you are working on gettin the ring,  hang in there.. It just takes patience and much, much time.... Or if your higher they say the OOT camp is more reliable, but i cant confirm that, never been there..  One thing that was probably a bonus for me was i never play til late... Like 3 eastern time..  Usually everytime i was in sro there was no more than 2 or 3 campin the ac including myself.. Some say the ac is more likely to spawn when more people are on but that may not be true... Last night from 3 am  til 10 there was two ac spawn... Also 3 terrorantuala which is a rare spawn and supposed to be on same spawn table as ac.. anyway you have heard all this on to my story  lol...<br><br> I went into sro and as soon as i got there sgs was out like crazy...  Well i figured what the hell so i would kill one.. as soon as i had time to get fm i would see another...  Well this was gettin me hyped cuz i had never seen sgs out that much here before... I managed to kill 5 out of the 7 that spawned right after another... Then a dry spell...  Nothing at all..  So i would run around with sow potions (definate plus to have for this place) and dmf(that way i could hover over the dunes better...  Around 5 or so a terror spawned and i decided to take it out....  This sucker had hps comparable to a sg or more...  So after it was dead i was meddin upon a sand dune...  then i saw the ac spawn right behind the dark elf camp... my heart hit the floor as i jumped up and ran over to it, but another guy already had it....  Trust me it sux to have this guy right in front of you  and you cant kill it.. :(  I was ready to log then... i mean he spawned not gonna spawn again soo right?  Well right after that a sg popped and someone took it out...  Then i saw a terror spawn and i thought hmm this is odd... I didn't take it i wanted to save my mana so i let someone else kill it...  They killed it and about 20 mins later another terror spawned...  Now this is really odd cuz this night was the first night i seen the thing and i had seen it 3 times...  I had been talkin to the guy who killed the ac before me and he said that i should stay cuz it has been known for the ac to spawn on a double spawn when terror spawns like that....  Well after that terror was gone i just sit on top of a sand dune and watched around me.. i was gettin dizzy from this...  about 1 hour later the ac popped and i was lucky cuz i was the only one in zone...  It was great...  I got my ring and gated back to ec  and made someone congrat me.. lol...  Anyway i got my ring late at night and was very patient...  If you see a terror chances are you will see an ac soon  so hang around...  It was worth it for me...<br><br>  Couple of things i want to mention...  First the two places i seen him spawn was...  In the little valley with the skeleton or whatever in it..  and Towards the Oasis zone... So he is prety much random.. dont let anyone tell you he will spawn here cuz they dont know... Also when you are there waiting they say to kill everything in sight...  Well it does seem to make things happen, but if someone is running around doin that sit back  save mana... dont want to be oom if the ac pops right?  But then again if everyone just sit back and waited nothing would happen  lol...  Ok  one other thing i want you to notice when you are in sro for this guy...  When it is night and is about to be morning notice that it always rains right before morning....  For real it does...  This is supposed to make it harder to see him from a distance and take away the kill stealing....  Well sorry to ramble so much.  this is what happened to me and if you want to ask about somethin feel free to...<br>&nbsp;<br>Sphoenix Darkfever</td></tr>
